Hidden Form Field:

is a hidden(invisible) textfield that is used for maintaining the state of a usr
<input type="hidden" name="user_name" value="Wahidullah Rahimi" />
it is simply a text file with type hidden that is not vissible to user, it is stored in browser and not seen by user , server can fetch it value using key/name
it is same as url rewriting , servlet1 generate a hidden form filed and sends it with response to the client
client can send the data to Servlet2, servlet2 can fetch the data from 2nd request of user


We can put specific data in simultanouse request and response for server to fetch and remember the user for state management purpose
